---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="About — Pendle Forest Orienteers"
  description="Pendle Forest Orienteers is a small British Orienteering club covering Burnley, Pendle, Rossendale, Accrington and Blackburn."
>

<main id="main">

  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow rise d-1">About PFO</p>
      <h1 class="rise d-2">A small club running a lot of events.</h1>
      <p class="page-lede rise d-3">PFO has been organising orienteering across East Lancashire since the 1970s. We're a member club of British Orienteering and the North West Orienteering Association, run entirely by volunteers, and welcome anyone who wants to give the sport a try.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info-block">
    <div class="info-wrap text-cols">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">What we do</p>
        <h2>Twelve to fifteen events a year, plus training.</h2>
        <p>Our calendar mixes midweek street and Snook-O events through spring and summer, weekend regional fixtures on the moors and forests around Burnley, and the headline <a href="/maps/brun-valley-forest-park">Brun Valley</a> Regional and Yvette Baker Trophy round each May. We also run a steady programme of training and coaching for members, from map-symbol workshops for newcomers up to night-orienteering technique for experienced runners.</p>
        <p>If we're not putting on an event, we're at someone else's — PFO members regularly travel to BO Major events, the JK, the British Champs, and the City Race Euro Tour.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Where we cover</p>
        <h2>Burnley to Blackburn, with the moors in between.</h2>
        <p>PFO maps and runs events across <strong>Burnley, Pendle, Rossendale, Accrington and Blackburn</strong>, plus a handful of venues further afield in the Forest of Bowland and the South Pennines.</p>
        <p>The <a href="/maps">map library</a> has every venue we currently use, with photos of the actual orienteering map and notes on access, parking, and terrain.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info-block alt">
    <div class="info-wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">The committee</p>
      <h2>Run by volunteers, every one of us.</h2>
      <p class="committee-intro">PFO has no paid staff. Every event, every map survey, every results upload, every newsletter and every training session happens because someone on the committee or in the membership puts the time in. We're always looking for help — if you can plan, control, organise registration, photograph, or run a social media account, please <a href="/contacts">get in touch</a>.</p>
      <p class="committee-cta">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/contacts">Meet the committee <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="info-block">
    <div class="info-wrap text-cols">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Become a member</p>
        <h2>Join PFO.</h2>
        <p>If you orienteer with us regularly, joining the club makes sense. You're insured, you pay less per event, and your results count toward both the British Orienteering ranking system and our own club awards. Membership is a single annual fee that covers PFO, NWOA and British Orienteering.</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/membership">Membership details <span class="arrow">→</span></a></p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">First time?</p>
        <h2>Try a Wednesday-evening street event.</h2>
        <p>Our local-level fixtures are deliberately friendly. Show up 30 minutes early, tell registration it's your first time, and someone will walk you through the map, the dibber, and the start. £6 for an adult, £1 for dibber hire if you don't have one.</p>
        <p><a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/newcomers">Newcomer guide <span class="arrow">→</span></a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding: clamp(40px, 5vw, 80px) var(--pad-x) clamp(40px, 4vw, 64px);
  }
  .page-hero-wrap { max-width: var(--max-w); margin: 0 auto; }
  .page-hero .eyebrow { color: var(--gold-muted); margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .page-hero .eyebrow::before { background: var(--plum); }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--ff-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(36px, 5vw, 64px);
    line-height: 1.0;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144, "SOFT" 20;
    margin: 0 0 20px 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    max-width: 24ch;
  }
  .page-lede {
    font-size: clamp(15px, 1.2vw, 17px);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .info-block { padding: clamp(48px, 5vw, 80px) var(--pad-x); }
  .info-block.alt { background: var(--paper-2); }
  .info-wrap { max-width: var(--max-w); margin: 0 auto; }
  .info-block .eyebrow { color: var(--gold-muted); margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .info-block .eyebrow::before { background: var(--plum); }
  .info-block h2 {
    font-family: var(--ff-display);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(26px, 3vw, 40px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-variation-settings: "opsz" 48, "SOFT" 20;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 18px 0;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .info-block p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 14px 0;
  }
  .info-block a { color: var(--navy); text-decoration: underline; text-decoration-color: var(--gold); text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .info-block a:hover { color: var(--plum); }
  .info-block strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }

  .text-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: clamp(32px, 5vw, 64px);
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    .text-cols { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }

  .committee-intro {
    max-width: 70ch;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
</style>
